Oh, I'm not denying
he saw something.

255
00:12:14,091 --> 00:12:16,691
Most likely, he slipped,
hit his head,

256
00:12:16,693 --> 00:12:19,161
got confused and saw a yak.

257
00:12:19,163 --> 00:12:21,330
Oh, okay, I get it now.

258
00:12:21,332 --> 00:12:24,299
Because if Migo is saying
he saw a smallfoot,

259
00:12:24,301 --> 00:12:26,368
then he's saying
a stone is wrong.

260
00:12:27,871 --> 00:12:29,872
Is that what
you're saying, Migo?

261
00:12:29,874 --> 00:12:31,339
That a stone is wrong?

262
00:12:31,341 --> 00:12:33,676
Nope! He is not saying that!

263
00:12:33,678 --> 00:12:36,310
Let me talk to him.
Kids, right?

264
00:12:36,312 --> 00:12:38,180
Migo, what are you doing?

265
00:12:38,182 --> 00:12:40,382
Challenging the Stonekeeper
in front of the whole village?

266
00:12:40,384 --> 00:12:42,850
Dad, what's the piece of advice
you're always giving me?

267
00:12:42,852 --> 00:12:44,085
Do what you're told.

268
00:12:44,087 --> 00:12:45,454
- The other one.
- Blend in.

269
00:12:45,456 --> 00:12:47,156
The other one.

270
00:12:47,158 --> 00:12:48,990
Follow the stones.
Be a cog. Do your part.

271
00:12:48,992 --> 00:12:50,392
Never disagree
with the Stonekeeper.

272
00:12:50,394 --> 00:12:52,127
Always be true!

273
00:12:52,129 --> 00:12:54,863
That was about hitting a gong.
Not challenging a stone.

274
00:12:54,865 --> 00:12:57,833
'Cause if it goes against
a stone, it can't be true!

275
00:12:57,835 --> 00:13:00,301
But if I say I didn't see
a smallfoot,

276
00:13:00,303 --> 00:13:01,869
then I'm lying.

277
00:13:01,871 --> 00:13:03,372
Migo...

278
00:13:03,374 --> 00:13:05,239
I thought you wanted
to be the next gong ringer.

279
00:13:05,241 --> 00:13:06,742
I do.

280
00:13:06,744 --> 00:13:08,911
Then are you still saying
a stone is wrong?

281
00:13:08,913 --> 00:13:12,247
If saying I saw a smallfoot
means that a stone is wrong,

282
00:13:12,249 --> 00:13:14,148
then I guess I am.

283
00:13:20,857 --> 00:13:23,224
Oh, Migo.

284
00:13:23,226 --> 00:13:27,028
It pains me to say this,
it truly does.

285
00:13:27,030 --> 00:13:29,034
But you leave me no choice.

286
00:13:30,934 --> 00:13:34,203
Disobeying the stones
is a grave offense.

287
00:13:34,205 --> 00:13:35,738
From this day forward,

288
00:13:35,740 --> 00:13:37,406
you will be banished
from the village!

289
00:13:37,408 --> 00:13:39,307
What?

290
00:13:39,309 --> 00:13:41,376
Until you are ready
to stand before us all

291
00:13:41,378 --> 00:13:43,112
and tell us the truth.

292
00:13:43,114 --> 00:13:46,013
I am telling the truth.

293
00:13:46,015 --> 00:13:48,316
That's all, everyone.
Back to work.

294
00:13:48,318 --> 00:13:49,917
Let's make it

295
00:13:49,919 --> 00:13:52,521
another perfect day.

296
00:13:52,523 --> 00:13:54,288
Stonekeeper, please.

297
00:13:54,290 --> 00:13:56,023
That's my son.

298
00:13:56,025 --> 00:13:58,259
Just give him a little time
alone out there to think.

299
00:13:58,261 --> 00:14:00,264
He'll come to his senses.

300
00:14:12,308 --> 00:14:14,343
- Sooze.
- Hey!

301
00:14:14,345 --> 00:14:16,945
You're banished, remember?
You know what that means.

302
00:14:16,947 --> 00:14:18,046
Yes, Thorp.

303
00:14:18,048 --> 00:14:19,848
You do? What does it mean?

304
00:14:19,850 --> 00:14:21,150
- Thorp!
- Coming!

305
00:14:21,152 --> 00:14:22,216
We'll circle back.

306
00:14:56,352 --> 00:14:58,554
Few can survive
the cold, brutal environment

307
00:14:58,556 --> 00:15:00,254
of the Himalayas,

308
00:15:00,256 --> 00:15:03,325
but this ingenious creature
defies the odds.

309
00:15:03,327 --> 00:15:05,560
The rare Himalayan
jumping spider!

310
00:15:05,562 --> 00:15:08,863
This week on
Percy Patterson's Wildlife!

311
00:15:08,865 --> 00:15:12,533
This agile arachnid can lay
1,000 eggs at a time

312
00:15:12,535 --> 00:15:15,305
and can jump 50 feet
into the air!

313
00:15:18,008 --> 00:15:20,142
There's an element
of mental preparation,

314
00:15:20,144 --> 00:15:21,344
I'm sure.

315
00:15:25,182 --> 00:15:26,480
It's attacking!

316
00:15:26,482 --> 00:15:28,050
Oh, no!

317
00:15:28,052 --> 00:15:29,517
The venom!
It's going to my brain!

318
00:15:29,519 --> 00:15:31,052
I can't feel my face.

319
00:15:31,054 --> 00:15:33,387
Keep rolling, keep rolling.

320
00:15:33,389 --> 00:15:34,522
Cut!

321
00:15:34,524 --> 00:15:37,025
I'm melting before your eyes.

322
00:15:37,027 --> 00:15:38,493
Percy!

323
00:15:38,495 --> 00:15:40,094
And we'll add an effect.
Melting, melting, melting.

324
00:15:40,096 --> 00:15:41,530
Percy!

325
00:15:41,532 --> 00:15:43,431
Cut this bit out.
I'm gonna shut one of my eyes.

326
00:15:43,433 --> 00:15:46,200
Oh, my eye! My eye!

327
00:15:46,202 --> 00:15:48,070
Cut! What are you doing?

328
00:15:48,072 --> 00:15:49,403
I'm saving our show.

329
00:15:49,405 --> 00:15:51,974
Me being attacked
would get huge ratings!

330
00:15:51,976 --> 00:15:54,910
Our show is educational
and enlightening!

331
00:15:54,912 --> 00:15:56,277
A show that promotes respect

332
00:15:56,279 --> 00:15:58,312
for our fellow creatures
on this planet.

333
00:15:58,314 --> 00:16:00,916
I know.
That's why no one's watching.

334
00:16:00,918 --> 00:16:02,517
That's why I don't watch.

335
00:16:02,519 --> 00:16:05,887
Look, Brenda, unless
our spider jumps, it's boring.

336
00:16:05,889 --> 00:16:07,455
Hey, it jumped!

337
00:16:10,894 --> 00:16:12,393
Now, that was exciting.
Did we film that?

338
00:16:12,395 --> 00:16:13,929
No, of course not.

339
00:16:13,931 --> 00:16:15,229
All right, I'll just have
to go over here

340
00:16:15,231 --> 00:16:17,599
and interview a piece
of bark, shall I?

341
00:16:17,601 --> 00:16:19,001
- Yeti.
- What?

342
00:16:19,003 --> 00:16:21,103
Plane crashed in the snow.

343
00:16:21,105 --> 00:16:23,137
Teeth, claws, huge!

344
00:16:23,139 --> 00:16:26,174
I saw a yeti!

345
00:16:29,312 --> 00:16:31,079
Yeti, you say?

346
00:16:31,081 --> 00:16:33,681
Let me buy you a drink and
you can tell me all about it.

347
00:16:33,683 --> 00:16:35,117
You believe me, right?

348
00:16:35,119 --> 00:16:36,618
Of course,
I believe you!

349
00:16:36,620 --> 00:16:38,320
You do?
You can trust me.

350
00:16:38,322 --> 00:16:39,457
I fly planes!

351
00:16:45,295 --> 00:16:48,062
Migo.

352
00:16:48,064 --> 00:16:49,196
Who's there?

353
00:16:49,198 --> 00:16:50,464
Migo.

354
00:16:50,466 --> 00:16:52,066
Hello?

355
00:16:52,068 --> 00:16:54,171
Smallfoot?
Is that you?

356
00:16:57,508 --> 00:17:00,508
Maybe you are going crazy.
No wonder no one believes you.

357
00:17:00,510 --> 00:17:02,009
We believe you.

358
00:17:02,011 --> 00:17:03,612
Hi.

359
00:17:03,614 --> 00:17:05,247
Migo.

360
00:17:05,249 --> 00:17:06,580
- Fleem!
- What?

361
00:17:06,582 --> 00:17:08,416
You guys.

362
00:17:08,418 --> 00:17:11,285
Is it just me, or does he look
disappointed that it's us?

363
00:17:11,287 --> 00:17:13,355
- You want proof that you saw what you saw?
- Yeah.

364
00:17:13,357 --> 00:17:14,622
We got proof.

365
00:17:14,624 --> 00:17:15,957
So, you believe me
that I saw a...

366
00:17:15,959 --> 00:17:18,426
A small...

367
00:17:18,428 --> 00:17:19,727
- They're listening.
- Who?

368
00:17:19,729 --> 00:17:21,562
The ears of oppression.

369
00:17:21,564 --> 00:17:23,397
Yeah.

370
00:17:23,399 --> 00:17:25,333
This way, stealth mode.

371
00:17:29,305 --> 00:17:31,976
Could this day get
any more bizarre?

372
00:17:32,609 --> 00:17:34,141
Is this too close?

373
00:17:34,143 --> 00:17:36,177
You know what you are now?

374
00:17:36,179 --> 00:17:37,412
One of us.

375
00:17:37,414 --> 00:17:39,013
Hey, wait up!

376
00:17:39,015 --> 00:17:43,385
One of us!
One of us! One of us!

377
00:17:43,387 --> 00:17:45,153
Now, don't tell Gwangi
I said this,

378
00:17:45,155 --> 00:17:46,455
but he's a bit paranoid.

379
00:17:46,457 --> 00:17:47,522
Fleem,
are you talking about me?

380
00:17:47,524 --> 00:17:49,657
Do you see what I mean?

381
00:17:49,659 --> 00:17:52,394
- Kolka talks to rocks like they can hear her.
- Fleem!

382
00:17:52,396 --> 00:17:54,695
I've been told I'm pesky,
annoying, and a real pain,

383
00:17:54,697 --> 00:17:57,232
but, hey, who listens
to their mom, right?

384
00:17:59,436 --> 00:18:00,702
Where are you taking me?

385
00:18:00,704 --> 00:18:02,704
Our leader requests a meeting.

386
00:18:02,706 --> 00:18:04,438
Wait, you have a leader? Who?

387
00:18:04,440 --> 00:18:05,543
You'll see.

388
00:18:11,415 --> 00:18:12,684
Oh, boy.

389
00:18:21,158 --> 00:18:22,159
He's here.

390
00:18:26,263 --> 00:18:27,495
Meechee?

391
00:18:27,497 --> 00:18:30,197
Welcome!
I'm really glad you're here.

392
00:18:30,199 --> 00:18:31,733
What?

393
00:18:31,735 --> 00:18:34,235
What is this place, exactly?

394
00:18:34,237 --> 00:18:37,472
The secret headquarters
of the S.E.S.

395
00:18:37,474 --> 00:18:38,740
The Esias?

396
00:18:38,742 --> 00:18:40,574
No, no, no.
It's three letters.

397
00:18:40,576 --> 00:18:42,043
Like S-E-S.

398
00:18:42,045 --> 00:18:43,712
Stands for
Smallfoot Exists, Suckas!

399
00:18:43,714 --> 00:18:45,246
Fleem.

400
00:18:45,248 --> 00:18:47,448
It's Smallfoot
Evidentiary Society.

401
00:18:47,450 --> 00:18:49,583
I mean, my name's got
a lot more pizzazz, but...

402
00:18:49,585 --> 00:18:51,685
Wait. You're, like,
a smallfoot club?

403
00:18:51,687 --> 00:18:53,187
And, hold on.

404
00:18:53,189 --> 00:18:54,522
You're the leader?

405
00:18:54,524 --> 00:18:55,791
But you're the
Stonekeeper's daughter.

406
00:18:55,793 --> 00:18:57,359
Look, I love my father,

407
00:18:57,361 --> 00:18:58,627
but he isn't exactly
what you would call

408
00:18:58,629 --> 00:19:00,128
open to new ideas.

409
00:19:00,130 --> 00:19:02,496
Because questions
lead to knowledge.

410
00:19:02,498 --> 00:19:04,499
And knowledge is power.

411
00:19:04,501 --> 00:19:07,135
So you don't just believe
in the smallfoot,

412
00:19:07,137 --> 00:19:08,770
you've been looking for one.

413
00:19:08,772 --> 00:19:10,705
Yes. You see all the X's?

414
00:19:10,707 --> 00:19:12,840
We have searched
the entire mountain

415
00:19:12,842 --> 00:19:14,208
for years trying to find one.

416
00:19:14,210 --> 00:19:15,543
Why are you looking for X's?

417
00:19:15,545 --> 00:19:16,778
We're not looking for X's.

418
00:19:16,780 --> 00:19:18,547
We're looking
for the smallfoot.

419
00:19:18,549 --> 00:19:19,848
And you have seen one.

420
00:19:19,850 --> 00:19:21,515
But I can't prove it.

421
00:19:21,517 --> 00:19:23,385
That is where we come in.

422
00:19:23,387 --> 00:19:25,454
Gwangi, show him the evidence.

423
00:19:26,523 --> 00:19:27,558
Here's your proof.

424
00:19:31,395 --> 00:19:33,494
First item, smallfoot pelt.

425
00:19:33,496 --> 00:19:35,730
Evidence suggests it sheds
its skin annually.

426
00:19:35,732 --> 00:19:40,135
Second item, smallfoot horn.
We believe it only has one.

427
00:19:40,137 --> 00:19:43,170
And then there's this.

428
00:19:43,172 --> 00:19:45,540
The scroll
of invisible wisdom.

429
00:19:45,542 --> 00:19:48,843
Just imagine the amazing stuff
they put on here.

430
00:19:48,845 --> 00:19:50,645
A bunch of crap,
if you ask me.

431
00:19:50,647 --> 00:19:52,746
This proves nothing!

432
00:19:52,748 --> 00:19:54,215
Show him the last one.

433
00:19:54,217 --> 00:19:55,716
It's the first piece
I ever found.

434
00:19:55,718 --> 00:19:57,586
It's the thing
that started all of this.

435
00:19:57,588 --> 00:19:59,120
That was a trigger.

436
00:19:59,122 --> 00:20:00,522
He's triggered!

437
00:20:01,859 --> 00:20:04,291
Look at your small foot.

438
00:20:04,293 --> 00:20:05,860
- You did see one.
- Where did it go?

439
00:20:05,862 --> 00:20:07,262
- I don't know!
- Think!

440
00:20:07,264 --> 00:20:08,864
- Reach into your memory!
- Slap him!

441
00:20:08,866 --> 00:20:11,332
No! It got whisked away
on the wind, over the clouds!

442
00:20:11,334 --> 00:20:13,403
Which way? Up?
Sideways? Where?

443
00:20:15,139 --> 00:20:16,338
Down!

444
00:20:16,340 --> 00:20:17,906
Did you say down?

445
00:20:17,908 --> 00:20:19,507
- Slap him!
- Fleem!

446
00:20:19,509 --> 00:20:21,208
Down! Of course!

447
00:20:21,210 --> 00:20:22,476
You know,
I have always thought

448
00:20:22,478 --> 00:20:23,778
it was weird
that a mountain floats

449
00:20:23,780 --> 00:20:25,347
when there's obviously

450
00:20:25,349 --> 00:20:27,182
some invisible force
pulling us downward

451
00:20:27,184 --> 00:20:28,382
and keeping everything
around us

452
00:20:28,384 --> 00:20:30,918
from drifting off
into the sky.

453
00:20:30,920 --> 00:20:32,587
Of course, this is just
a theory.

454
00:20:32,589 --> 00:20:35,423
But that's why
we haven't found one up here.

455
00:20:35,425 --> 00:20:40,494
Because it's down here.
Below the clouds.

456
00:20:40,496 --> 00:20:44,331
And if you want proof,
that's where we need to go.

457
00:20:44,333 --> 00:20:46,837
In...
In the nothing?

458
00:20:48,539 --> 00:20:50,338
You're crazy.

459
00:20:50,340 --> 00:20:51,572
Don't call me crazy.

460
00:20:51,574 --> 00:20:53,175
Yeah. Never call
a crazy guy crazy.

461
00:20:53,177 --> 00:20:54,542
You want to know why
it's called the nothing?

462
00:20:54,544 --> 00:20:56,410
Because there's nothing
down there!

463
00:20:56,412 --> 00:20:57,646
Why do you believe that?

464
00:20:57,648 --> 00:20:59,380
Because it's in the stones.

465
00:20:59,382 --> 00:21:01,483
So is the one that says
there's no smallfoot.

466
00:21:01,485 --> 00:21:02,650
And yet, you saw one.

467
00:21:02,652 --> 00:21:03,918
Yeah. Why is there a stone

468
00:21:03,920 --> 00:21:05,587
that says something
doesn't exist?

469
00:21:05,589 --> 00:21:07,355
Doesn't that just prove
that it actually does?

470
00:21:07,357 --> 00:21:10,591
And if one stone is wrong,
then others could be as well.

471
00:21:10,593 --> 00:21:12,726
What? Other stones?

472
00:21:12,728 --> 00:21:13,928
How many do you
think are wrong?

473
00:21:13,930 --> 00:21:15,397
The whole robe.

474
00:21:16,867 --> 00:21:18,827
You know what? This whole
thing's insane. I'm out.

475
00:21:19,468 --> 00:21:20,935
Migo, wait.

476
00:21:20,937 --> 00:21:22,670
Hey, I just wanna prove
that I saw a smallfoot

477
00:21:22,672 --> 00:21:24,339
so I can get un-banished.

478
00:21:24,341 --> 00:21:26,241
But you, you wanna, what?

479
00:21:26,243 --> 00:21:27,943
Tear down everything
our world is built on?

480
00:21:27,945 --> 00:21:31,512
It's not just about
tearing down old ideas.

481
00:21:31,514 --> 00:21:33,447
It's about finding new ones.

482
00:21:34,584 --> 00:21:35,919
You know what, come with me.

483
00:21:44,328 --> 00:21:45,926
<i>Take a look around</i>

484
00:21:45,928 --> 00:21:48,830
<i>And see the world
we think we know</i>

485
00:21:48,832 --> 00:21:52,234
<i>And then look closer</i>

486
00:21:53,704 --> 00:21:55,770
<i>There's more to life
than meets the eye</i>

487
00:21:55,772 --> 00:21:58,005
<i>A beauty to behold</i>

488
00:21:58,007 --> 00:22:03,514
<i>It's all much bigger
than we know</i>

489
00:22:05,349 --> 00:22:08,819
<i>It's only just beginning
to unfold</i>

490
00:22:09,919 --> 00:22:12,020
<i>So let it all unfold</i>

491
00:22:12,022 --> 00:22:16,791
<i>Far beyond all reason
in your mind</i>

492
00:22:16,793 --> 00:22:21,529
<i>There's a world mysterious,
there for you to find</i>

493
00:22:21,531 --> 00:22:26,268
<i>All these questions
that we always had</i>

494
00:22:26,270 --> 00:22:28,535
<i>All we are is curious</i>

495
00:22:28,537 --> 00:22:30,672
<i>There's nothing
wrong with that</i>

496
00:22:30,674 --> 00:22:35,443
<i>So go 'round every corner</i>

497
00:22:35,445 --> 00:22:39,813
<i>Search every part of the sky</i>

498
00:22:39,815 --> 00:22:44,521
<i>'Cause a life
that's full of wonder</i>

499
00:22:45,789 --> 00:22:48,359
<i>Is a wonderful life</i>

500
00:23:01,304 --> 00:23:02,870
<i>Dig beneath the surface</i>

501
00:23:02,872 --> 00:23:05,773
<i>Find the lessons
there to learn</i>

502
00:23:05,775 --> 00:23:10,544
<i>And then dig deeper</i>

503
00:23:10,546 --> 00:23:15,416
<i>Feed your intuition,
don't leave any stone unturned</i>

504
00:23:15,418 --> 00:23:20,257
<i>Be the seeker of the truth</i>

505
00:23:22,325 --> 00:23:25,595
<i>Listen when you hear it
calling you</i>

506
00:23:26,662 --> 00:23:28,963
<i>You know it's calling you</i>

507
00:23:28,965 --> 00:23:33,835
<i>Far beyond all reason
in your mind</i>

508
00:23:33,837 --> 00:23:38,473
<i>There's a world mysterious,
there for you to find</i>

509
00:23:38,475 --> 00:23:43,043
<i>All these questions
that we always have</i>

510
00:23:43,045 --> 00:23:45,512
<i>All we are is curious</i>

511
00:23:45,514 --> 00:23:47,581
<i>There's nothing
wrong with that</i>

512
00:23:47,583 --> 00:23:52,454
