987
00:50:02,357 --> 00:50:04,123
- How did you get it here?
- What does it eat?

988
00:50:04,125 --> 00:50:06,159
How does it think
with such a tiny little brain?

989
00:50:06,161 --> 00:50:09,561
Honestly, I have just as many
questions as you do.

990
00:50:09,563 --> 00:50:11,163
- Where is its horn?
- Is that its ear?

991
00:50:11,165 --> 00:50:12,465
Does it want a bite of fruit?

992
00:50:12,467 --> 00:50:14,199
How is it here if a stone
says it can't be?

993
00:50:14,201 --> 00:50:18,471
<i>It's all much bigger
than we know</i>

994
00:50:18,473 --> 00:50:19,672
- How?
- Why?

995
00:50:19,674 --> 00:50:21,273
What do you mean?

996
00:50:21,275 --> 00:50:23,176
<i>It's only just beginning
to unfold</i>

997
00:50:23,178 --> 00:50:24,978
