1263
01:03:14,214 --> 01:03:15,947
Just stop asking questions!

1264
01:03:15,949 --> 01:03:17,750
Stop asking questions?

1265
01:03:20,288 --> 01:03:22,387
Attention, everyone!

1266
01:03:22,389 --> 01:03:24,259
The Stonekeeper
has an announcement.

1267
01:03:25,359 --> 01:03:26,859
What's going on? Do you know?

1268
01:03:26,861 --> 01:03:28,127
'Cause you look
like you know something.

1269
01:03:28,129 --> 01:03:30,328
Just stop. Please.

1270
01:03:30,330 --> 01:03:31,996
Well, well, well,

1271
01:03:31,998 --> 01:03:33,833
what an interesting day
it's been.

1272
01:03:33,835 --> 01:03:37,203
A day full of excitement
and questions.

1273
01:03:37,205 --> 01:03:39,804
So many questions.

1274
01:03:39,806 --> 01:03:41,773
I must admit,
the events of the day

1275
01:03:41,775 --> 01:03:43,442
even had me asking a few.

1276
01:03:43,444 --> 01:03:45,311
I smell cover-up.

1277
01:03:45,313 --> 01:03:47,179
So I asked Migo to join me

1278
01:03:47,181 --> 01:03:50,516
so I could question him
about his amazing discovery.

1279
01:03:50,518 --> 01:03:53,418
And together, we've reached
the same conclusion.

1280
01:03:53,420 --> 01:03:55,221
Migo, tell them
what we learned.

1281
01:03:55,223 --> 01:03:56,288
Yeah.

1282
01:03:59,793 --> 01:04:03,295
The thing is, see...

1283
01:04:03,297 --> 01:04:04,929
Yeah, it's...

1284
01:04:04,931 --> 01:04:08,236
What I was gonna
tell you is...

1285
01:04:13,940 --> 01:04:15,507
It's not a smallfoot.

1286
01:04:15,509 --> 01:04:17,810
Wait. What?

1287
01:04:17,812 --> 01:04:20,246
Yeah. I was wrong,
I got confused,

1288
01:04:20,248 --> 01:04:21,980
and the Stonekeeper
figured it out.

1289
01:04:21,982 --> 01:04:23,382
It's actually a type of yak.

1290
01:04:23,384 --> 01:04:25,049
A yak?

1291
01:04:25,051 --> 01:04:26,786
Migo found a rare breed that

1292
01:04:26,788 --> 01:04:28,887
- even I didn't know about.
- No...

1293
01:04:28,889 --> 01:04:31,422
A red-coated
pygmy hairless yak.

1294
01:04:31,424 --> 01:04:33,491
You know this is not a yak.

1295
01:04:33,493 --> 01:04:36,427
As you can see,
its existence is confirmed

1296
01:04:36,429 --> 01:04:37,866
in stone.

1297
01:04:41,368 --> 01:04:43,002
What is happening?

1298
01:04:43,004 --> 01:04:45,471
The stones have protected us
for generations.

1299
01:04:45,473 --> 01:04:47,139
But we've been ignoring them.

1300
01:04:47,141 --> 01:04:48,406
No one's been feeding

1301
01:04:48,408 --> 01:04:49,909
the great
mountain mammoths today.

1302
01:04:49,911 --> 01:04:51,210
He's right.

1303
01:04:51,212 --> 01:04:53,279
And because of that,
we are sinking.

1304
01:04:53,281 --> 01:04:54,913
I don't wanna sink!

1305
01:04:54,915 --> 01:04:57,382
Garry, you're right
to be afraid.

1306
01:04:57,384 --> 01:04:58,918
Everyone,
listen to Garry.

1307
01:05:00,154 --> 01:05:01,252
I don't wanna sink
into the nothing!

1308
01:05:01,254 --> 01:05:02,453
These are lies, Migo.

1309
01:05:02,455 --> 01:05:04,089
We saw you
go below the clouds.

1310
01:05:04,091 --> 01:05:06,458
I didn't.
I fell into the clouds

1311
01:05:06,460 --> 01:05:08,226
and I found him
inside of a cave.

1312
01:05:08,228 --> 01:05:09,360
What?

1313
01:05:09,362 --> 01:05:10,929
Don't listen to him.

1314
01:05:10,931 --> 01:05:12,398
This is all part of
a massive cover-up!

1315
01:05:12,400 --> 01:05:13,565
Please, just...

1316
01:05:13,567 --> 01:05:14,567
We're all part of
a big machine.

1317
01:05:14,569 --> 01:05:16,168
Dude, no. Come on, stop!

1318
01:05:16,170 --> 01:05:17,436
In fact, I think it might be
a big machine

1319
01:05:17,438 --> 01:05:19,170
- that's down there!
- You need to stop!

1320
01:05:19,172 --> 01:05:20,339
- It does sound like a machine!
- I thought so too!

1321
01:05:20,341 --> 01:05:21,421
- You heard me!
- Just stop!

1322
01:05:23,043 --> 01:05:25,578
A big machine.

1323
01:05:25,580 --> 01:05:27,378
Right!

1324
01:05:27,380 --> 01:05:29,415
Let's all listen to Gwangi
and his whacked-out theories

1325
01:05:29,417 --> 01:05:31,516
because we all know
that Gwangi is

1326
01:05:31,518 --> 01:05:33,418
just straight-up crazy.

1327
01:05:33,420 --> 01:05:35,320
- What?
- Don't call him crazy.

1328
01:05:35,322 --> 01:05:37,022
Come on, are we really
gonna listen to these guys?

1329
01:05:37,024 --> 01:05:38,156
They're the village weirdos,
right?

1330
01:05:38,158 --> 01:05:39,891
We all know that.

1331
01:05:39,893 --> 01:05:41,960
They're just trying to prove
all the stones wrong.

1332
01:05:41,962 --> 01:05:43,628
But if we don't follow
the stones,

1333
01:05:43,630 --> 01:05:46,065
really bad things can happen.

1334
01:05:47,500 --> 01:05:50,201
Well said, Migo.
That's the truth.

1335
01:05:50,203 --> 01:05:51,904
The truth?

1336
01:05:51,906 --> 01:05:54,810
I don't think anybody around
here cares what that is.

1337
01:05:57,043 --> 01:05:58,610
Guys, wait.

1338
01:05:58,612 --> 01:06:00,511
Migo, give him to me.

1339
01:06:00,513 --> 01:06:01,647
Wait,
what are you doing?

1340
01:06:03,350 --> 01:06:05,049
No, no, no! He need warmth
and he can't breathe!

1341
01:06:05,051 --> 01:06:06,185
Meechee.

1342
01:06:06,187 --> 01:06:07,920
Why are you doing this?

1343
01:06:07,922 --> 01:06:11,159
This is something
we should discuss inside.

1344
01:06:12,326 --> 01:06:13,495
Inside.

1345
01:06:16,596 --> 01:06:18,464
Yes, Father.

1346
01:06:18,466 --> 01:06:20,465
Meechee, we need to talk.

1347
01:06:20,467 --> 01:06:22,571
I think you've said enough.

1348
01:06:24,071 --> 01:06:25,503
Okay, everyone.

1349
01:06:25,505 --> 01:06:28,206
Now everything can go back
to the way it was.

1350
01:06:28,208 --> 01:06:31,944
Everyone, back to work.
The village won't run itself.

1351
01:06:31,946 --> 01:06:34,413
The smallfoot, what are you
gonna do with him?

1352
01:06:34,415 --> 01:06:37,415
We're taking him back to
the cave where you found him.

1353
01:06:37,417 --> 01:06:39,485
But I didn't find him
in a cave.

1354
01:06:39,487 --> 01:06:43,087
But you said you did,
so they believe you.

1355
01:06:43,089 --> 01:06:44,592
You've done a good thing,
Migo.

1356
01:06:59,272 --> 01:07:00,507
Stonekeeper, wait!

1357
01:07:02,109 --> 01:07:03,111
No!

1358
01:07:05,179 --> 01:07:06,947
You've done your job, Migo.

1359
01:07:07,614 --> 01:07:09,417
Go home.

1360
01:07:50,324 --> 01:07:52,357
Migo?

1361
01:07:52,359 --> 01:07:55,027
What's wrong?
What are you doing?

1362
01:07:55,029 --> 01:07:57,332
I was just thinking
about Stone 15.

1363
01:07:59,100 --> 01:08:00,565
Ignorance is bliss?

1364
01:08:00,567 --> 01:08:03,268
Yeah. That one's true.

1365
01:08:03,270 --> 01:08:05,371
Ignorance is bliss.

1366
01:08:05,373 --> 01:08:07,473
Or at least it was.

1367
01:08:07,475 --> 01:08:09,007
I was pretty happy

1368
01:08:09,009 --> 01:08:11,043
when I didn't know
about the smallfoot.

1369
01:08:11,045 --> 01:08:12,444
Or the S.E.S.

1370
01:08:12,446 --> 01:08:15,714
Or how amazing
Meechee really is.

1371
01:08:15,716 --> 01:08:17,315
And I'm pretty sure
I'd be happier

1372
01:08:17,317 --> 01:08:19,250
not knowing that they hate me.

1373
01:08:19,252 --> 01:08:23,023
Or that I lied
and betrayed them all.

1374
01:08:25,126 --> 01:08:26,628
I miss being ignorant.

1375
01:08:28,162 --> 01:08:29,794
So let's just, you know,

1376
01:08:29,796 --> 01:08:31,663
go back to the way
things were.

1377
01:08:31,665 --> 01:08:34,066
With one change.

1378
01:08:34,068 --> 01:08:36,735
I'll be the gong ringer
from now on.

1379
01:08:36,737 --> 01:08:38,771
Maybe banging my head
into that thing

1380
01:08:38,773 --> 01:08:41,373
will make all of these
feelings go away.

1381
01:08:41,375 --> 01:08:43,307
Oh, yeah.
You'll pretty much go numb.

1382
01:08:43,309 --> 01:08:44,575
You won't feel a thing.

1383
01:08:44,577 --> 01:08:47,982
Good. Because I feel like
such a jerk.

1384
01:08:53,354 --> 01:08:54,786
Okay.

1385
01:08:54,788 --> 01:08:57,088
Now, you remember
the advice I gave you, right?

1386
01:08:57,090 --> 01:08:58,757
First, check the wind.

1387
01:08:58,759 --> 01:09:00,659
Pretty easy
to get blown off course.

1388
01:09:00,661 --> 01:09:02,998
Wind, check.

1389
01:09:03,831 --> 01:09:06,164
And you gotta true your aim.

1390
01:09:06,166 --> 01:09:08,801
You'll never succeed
if your aim isn't true.

1391
01:09:08,803 --> 01:09:10,768
Aim, check.

1392
01:09:10,770 --> 01:09:12,337
And don't forget,

1393
01:09:12,339 --> 01:09:14,639
even though you know
it's gonna hurt,

1394
01:09:14,641 --> 01:09:16,678
you gotta hit it head-on.

1395
01:09:22,616 --> 01:09:24,749
He's in there.

1396
01:09:24,751 --> 01:09:26,185
She's in there.

1397
01:09:26,187 --> 01:09:27,255
But...

1398
01:09:29,189 --> 01:09:32,191
You already woke
the village, son.

1399
01:09:32,193 --> 01:09:34,362
Now, go make sure
they stay awake.

1400
01:09:36,764 --> 01:09:38,297
I love you, Dad.

1401
01:09:38,299 --> 01:09:40,298
I love you too, son.

1402
01:09:40,300 --> 01:09:41,535
Now, say the word.

1403
01:09:43,304 --> 01:09:44,305
Launch!

1404
01:09:56,382 --> 01:09:58,153
Meechee, I am so sor...

1405
01:10:00,587 --> 01:10:02,120
Oh, no.

1406
01:10:02,122 --> 01:10:03,621
Meechee?

1407
01:10:03,623 --> 01:10:05,393
What are you doing here?

1408
01:10:15,803 --> 01:10:16,869
Meechee.

1409
01:10:16,871 --> 01:10:18,105
Where's the smallfoot?

1410
01:10:21,274 --> 01:10:24,446
Hold on, little guy, okay?
You're almost home.

1411
01:10:33,420 --> 01:10:36,420
Yeah, so Meechee
took the smallfoot.

1412
01:10:38,158 --> 01:10:39,857
And convinced me
I have a lot of anger issues

1413
01:10:39,859 --> 01:10:42,861
because of something
called a father complex.

1414
01:10:42,863 --> 01:10:44,295
I don't know, something about

1415
01:10:44,297 --> 01:10:46,231
not getting enough hugs
as a kid.

1416
01:10:46,233 --> 01:10:51,203
Really doing some serious
processing right now, Dad.

1417
01:10:51,205 --> 01:10:52,870
What have I done?

1418
01:10:52,872 --> 01:10:54,839
Open the door!

1419
01:10:59,180 --> 01:11:00,913
Guys!

1420
01:11:00,915 --> 01:11:03,182
Guys! You have to help me!

1421
01:11:03,184 --> 01:11:05,253
Meechee's taken the smallfoot
below the clouds!

1422
01:11:07,821 --> 01:11:10,289
Look, I'm sorry.
I didn't mean what I said.

1423
01:11:10,291 --> 01:11:12,857
I can explain everything.
After we find Meechee.

1424
01:11:12,859 --> 01:11:15,360
She's in danger.
You have to believe me!

1425
01:11:15,362 --> 01:11:18,396
Why should we believe you?
You lied.

1426
01:11:18,398 --> 01:11:19,731
Friends don't do that.

1427
01:11:19,733 --> 01:11:21,933
Or stab you in the back
and call you crazy

1428
01:11:21,935 --> 01:11:23,669
in front of the whole village.

1429
01:11:23,671 --> 01:11:26,774
You acted like me.
I expect more from you.

1430
01:11:28,908 --> 01:11:30,844
You're right. I lied.

1431
01:11:33,546 --> 01:11:35,547
You know, you've always
searched for the truth.

1432
01:11:35,549 --> 01:11:36,949
No matter what anybody said.

1433
01:11:36,951 --> 01:11:38,950
They laughed at you,
they called you names.

1434
01:11:38,952 --> 01:11:41,219
Wait. What names?

1435
01:11:41,221 --> 01:11:43,925
But you never let fear
get in the way.

1436
01:11:45,960 --> 01:11:47,862
That's what
I should have done.

1437
01:11:52,599 --> 01:11:54,535
And it's what
I'm gonna do now.

1438
01:11:56,870 --> 01:11:58,773
Migo!

1439
01:12:00,573 --> 01:12:03,443
Wait! What names?

1440
01:12:15,823 --> 01:12:18,557
Oh, Meechee, where are you?

1441
01:12:27,768 --> 01:12:29,301
- Kolka!
- Hi!

1442
01:12:29,303 --> 01:12:31,703
Hi! Wait.
If you're here, that means...

1443
01:12:36,277 --> 01:12:38,610
Man! That is
a long way down!

1444
01:12:39,747 --> 01:12:40,748
Guys!

1445
01:12:43,617 --> 01:12:44,816
You came!

1446
01:12:44,818 --> 01:12:47,319
Of course we came.
For Meechee.

1447
01:12:48,855 --> 01:12:50,688
Yeah. Yeah, I know.

1448
01:12:50,690 --> 01:12:53,458
And a little bit for you.
But mostly Meechee.

1449
01:12:53,460 --> 01:12:55,893
Thank you. Even you, Fleem.

1450
01:12:55,895 --> 01:12:57,329
Wait, where's Fleem?

1451
01:12:57,331 --> 01:12:59,330
Okay, pros and cons.

1452
01:12:59,332 --> 01:13:00,731
Pro, Migo needs you.

1453
01:13:00,733 --> 01:13:02,700
Con, you're useless to him
if you're dead.

1454
01:13:03,937 --> 01:13:06,804
Cons, one, pros, zero.
Okay. Pro.

1455
01:13:06,806 --> 01:13:08,706
Yeah, Fleem sucks.

1456
01:13:08,708 --> 01:13:10,609
We can't wait.
We have to find Meechee

1457
01:13:10,611 --> 01:13:12,447
right now
before someone else does.

1458
01:13:15,549 --> 01:13:17,749
It's so big.

1459
01:13:17,751 --> 01:13:19,151
How do we even know
she landed here?

1460
01:13:22,956 --> 01:13:24,690
Okay, little guy.

1461
01:13:24,692 --> 01:13:27,325
You can breathe easy now.

1462
01:13:27,327 --> 01:13:28,328
You're home. See?

1463
01:13:29,330 --> 01:13:30,331
Home.

1464
01:13:31,698 --> 01:13:33,467
What is that?

1465
01:13:40,373 --> 01:13:41,908
Wait, where am I?

1466
01:13:49,515 --> 01:13:51,016
What?

1467
01:13:51,018 --> 01:13:53,084
Oh, no. No, no, no, no, no.

1468
01:13:55,389 --> 01:13:56,391
Okay.

1469
01:13:58,625 --> 01:14:00,124
- Brenda?
- Percy?

1470
01:14:03,930 --> 01:14:05,129
Percy! You're alive!

1471
01:14:05,131 --> 01:14:06,831
You're alive!

1472
01:14:06,833 --> 01:14:08,366
Oh, my gosh,
you are alive, aren't you?

1473
01:14:08,368 --> 01:14:09,868
Not dead. Raring to go.

1474
01:14:09,870 --> 01:14:11,535
Know that I risked my life

1475
01:14:11,537 --> 01:14:12,803
in pursuit of
something extraordinary.

1476
01:14:12,805 --> 01:14:14,039
Something bigger than us.

1477
01:14:14,041 --> 01:14:15,507
My video.

1478
01:14:15,509 --> 01:14:16,874
I uploaded it
like you told me to

1479
01:14:16,876 --> 01:14:19,378
and it went totally viral!

1480
01:14:19,380 --> 01:14:21,679
It was real, right?
I mean, I have the suit.

1481
01:14:21,681 --> 01:14:23,981
You found a yeti.

1482
01:14:23,983 --> 01:14:25,784
My phone has been ringing
like crazy.

1483
01:14:25,786 --> 01:14:27,486
Everyone wants you.

1484
01:14:27,488 --> 01:14:29,490
Haven't you checked
your messages?

1485
01:14:31,992 --> 01:14:33,090
My life in pursuit

1486
01:14:33,092 --> 01:14:35,627
of something extraordinary.

1487
01:14:35,629 --> 01:14:36,828
Percy, my favorite client! It's
your agent. I want you back. Call me.

1488
01:14:36,830 --> 01:14:38,629
This is Mark Birden

1489
01:14:38,631 --> 01:14:40,531
from the National Geographic
Society. Call me!

1490
01:14:40,533 --> 01:14:42,700
Percy, it's your dad!
I'm no longer ashamed of you!

1491
01:14:42,702 --> 01:14:44,736
Hi, this is the New York
Times calling again...

1492
01:14:44,738 --> 01:14:45,937
I got your number
from a friend of a friend.

1493
01:14:45,939 --> 01:14:47,539
I saw your video.

1494
01:14:52,946 --> 01:14:55,045
Percy,
it's Gayle at the network.

1495
01:14:55,047 --> 01:14:56,580
I saw your video!

1496
01:14:56,582 --> 01:14:58,682
If you can
get that yeti alive,

1497
01:14:58,684 --> 01:15:00,518
you and your show are saved!

1498
01:15:01,854 --> 01:15:03,088
This is
everything you wanted.

1499
01:15:04,190 --> 01:15:06,094
Wait, the yeti is here?

1500
01:15:08,694 --> 01:15:10,762
I can't believe
what I'm looking at.

1501
01:15:10,764 --> 01:15:12,463
This is incredible!

1502
01:15:15,601 --> 01:15:17,004
What is that?

1503
01:15:18,205 --> 01:15:20,038
So pretty.

1504
01:15:20,040 --> 01:15:22,973
Oh, my gosh, a baby smallfoot!

1505
01:15:22,975 --> 01:15:24,942
You are so cute!

1506
01:15:26,846 --> 01:15:29,847
Wow, you are so limber!

1507
01:15:29,849 --> 01:15:31,651
Yeah!

1508
01:15:33,053 --> 01:15:34,455
Wait, you're not real,
are you?

1509
01:15:37,657 --> 01:15:40,224
Super pointy.

1510
01:15:40,226 --> 01:15:42,460
Oh, it's so pretty.

1511
01:15:42,462 --> 01:15:44,463
Another smallfoot!

1512
01:15:44,465 --> 01:15:46,097
How many of you are there?

1513
01:15:46,099 --> 01:15:48,200
Oh, a lot.

1514
01:15:48,202 --> 01:15:49,804
Hi.

1515
01:15:55,608 --> 01:15:58,477
Those are fast.

1516
01:16:09,989 --> 01:16:12,190
Guys, I've looked everywhere.
Meechee's not here.

1517
01:16:12,192 --> 01:16:13,761
Yeah, I think I found her.

1518
01:16:16,529 --> 01:16:18,896
Oh, this is amazing!

1519
01:16:25,506 --> 01:16:26,741
Hey...

1520
01:16:27,741 --> 01:16:29,508
Oh, no, no, no.

